{"questionId":"14026","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>OAB is a sector of the circle with centre O and radius <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span>, as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f4e4c153f29f32c4a40aff5f6977e07564e20460.png\"></p>\n<p>The angle AOB is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\theta \">\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span> radians, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0 < \\theta&nbsp; < \\frac{\\pi }{2}\">\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>The point C lies on OA and OA is perpendicular to BC.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that the area of triangle OBC is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{5}\"> <mfrac> <mn>3</mn> <mn>5</mn> </mfrac> </math></span>&nbsp;of the area of sector OAB, find <em>θ</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid attempt to express the relationship between the areas (seen anywhere) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;OCB =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{3}{5}\"> <mfrac> <mn>3</mn> <mn>5</mn> </mfrac> </math></span>OBA ,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{1}{2}{r^2}\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta \\,{\\text{cos}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{3}{5} \\times \\frac{1}{2}{r^2}\\theta \"> <mfrac> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>sin</mtext> </mrow> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mi>θ</mi> <mspace width=\"thinm